Installing Java on OS X
- In terminal
java -version
- If java  is present we can update it to the latest version
- Go to the following link
http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/index.html
- Click on JDK and select the appropriate download
- And install it.

* Where Java is installed:
- Go to finder window
- Go to /Library/java
- Go to JavaVirtualMachines -> Contents -> Home folder
- The bin folder contains all the command line tools
